1 ) Clone or Download the Repo

bash
git clone https://github.com/FlickM10/MyCanvasInfinity.git
Or download the ZIP from GitHub and extract it.

2 ) Open Chrome Extensions Page

In Chrome, go to: chrome://extensions/

Toggle Developer mode (top right).

3 ) Load the Extension

Click “Load unpacked”.

Select the project folder (the one containing manifest.json).

4 ) Pin the Extension

Click the puzzle‑piece icon in Chrome’s toolbar.

Pin MyCanvasInfinity so it’s always visible.

5 ) Use on Canvas

Log into your Canvas LMS.

Click the extension icon → the popup will open.

Assignments will be extracted, analyzed, and displayed in the chat‑style UI with priority badges and summaries.

6 ) Debugging / Logs

Right‑click the popup → Inspect → check the Console for logs.

This shows assignment extraction, AI calls, and caching in real time
